  "description": "Decentralized identity via Renown, DID-based authentication, cryptographic action signing, and the layered permission model that secures Powerhouse documents.",
  "orientation": "Security in Powerhouse is built on decentralized identity rather than centralized user databases. The Renown system creates DIDs from Ethereum wallets, giving users self-sovereign identities that work across any reactor without a central authority. Every operation can be cryptographically signed \u2014 either at the header level for transport integrity or at the individual action level for non-repudiation \u2014 and the ReactorClient handles this signing transparently. On top of identity, a layered authorization model controls who can do what: from broad drive-level permissions down to fine-grained operation-level access, with group support for organizational structures. This MOC maps the complete security story from wallet connection through identity creation to permission enforcement.",
